"Primary procurement units" means:
the State Treasurer;
the Department of Budget and Management;
the Department of General Services;
the Department of Transportation;
the Department of Information Technology;
the University System of Maryland;
the Maryland Port Commission;
the Department of Public Safety and Correctional Services;
the Morgan State University; and
the St. Mary's College of Maryland.

section.section:
"Procurement contract" does not include:
a collective bargaining agreement with an employee organization;
an agreement with a contractual employee, as defined in § 1-101(d) of the State Personnel and Pensions Article;
a Medicaid, Judicare, or similar reimbursement contract for which law sets:
a Medicaid contract with a managed care organization, as defined in § 15-101(e) of the Health - General Article as to which regulations adopted by the Department establish:

"Services" does not include:
construction related services;
architectural services;
engineering services; or
energy performance contract services.

"Supplies" means:
insurance;
tangible personal property;
printing; and
services necessarily associated with insurance or tangible personal property.
